# Overview

This page documents the `{{ name }}` OpenHound source, including its architecture, resource relationships and exported OpenGraph assets. The source extracts data from {{ name }} and transforms it into the standardized OpenGraph format. Use the visual diagram below to understand how nodes relate to each other, then explore the exported DLT [resources](resources.md) and invidual assets.

## Visual overview
The diagram below shows the relationships between OpenGraph nodes and assets that are part of the {{ name }} source. This diagram is automatically generated by each resource/asset that is wrapped with the `@app.asset` decorator.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
{% for r in graph_resources %}
{%- if r.node and r.node.icon and r.node.kind %}
    {{ r.node.kind }}["fa:fa-{{ r.node.icon }}"]:::bhNode
{% endif %}
{%- endfor %}
{%- for r in graph_resources %}
{%- for e in r.get('edges', []) %}
    {{ e.start }} -- {{e.kind}} --> {{e.end}}
{%- endfor %}
{%- endfor %}
```

